message.content:
A keyboard is a device for inputting text, numbers, and other symbols into a computer or other electronic device. It typically features a layout of alphanumeric keys, as well as various function keys and control keys.
The keyboard usually has a rectangular shape and is composed of various materials, including plastic, metal, and silicone.
The keys on the keyboard are usually made of plastic or a similar material and are often black or white in color.
The surface of the keyboard often has a matte finish to reduce glare and prevent fingerprints.
Keyboards are commonly used in offices, schools, and homes for typing and other input tasks, and are often integrated into laptops and computer peripherals.
Some keyboards may have additional features such as backlit keys, programmable keys, and multimedia buttons.
The QWERTY keyboard layout, which is the most common type, was first introduced by typewriters in the late 1800s and has been widely used ever since.
